uestions%20in%20Switzerland%2C%20where%20active%20euthanasia%20is%20illegal%2C%20yet%20assisted%20dying%20has%20been%20permitted%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20day%20the%20pod%20was%20used%2C%20Switzerland's%20Interior%20Minister%2C%20Elisabeth%20Baume-Schneider%2C%20told%20lawmakers%20that%20the%20Sarco%20remained%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20legal%2C%E2%80%9D%20leading%20to%20a%20fresh%20debate%20around%20its%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20take%20a%20look%20at%20what%20the%20Sarco%20suicide%20pod%20is%2C%20how%20it%20works%2C%20and%20the%20controversies.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20Sarco%20Pod%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.exitinternational.net%2Fsarco%2F%5C%22%3ESarco%20pod%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20short%20for%20sarcophagus%2C%20is%20a%20controversial%20euthanasia%20device%20that%20has%20attracted%20significant%20attention%20due%20to%20its%20innovative%20design%20and%20intended%20use.%20This%203D-printed%2C%20detachable%20capsule%20is%20mounted%20on%20a%20stand%20and%20contains%20a%20canister%20of%20liquid%20nitrogen%2C%20allowing%20individuals%20to%20end%20their%20lives%20through%20inert%20gas%20asphyxiation.%20First%20introduced%20in%20Switzerland%20in%202019%2C%20the%20capsule%20offers%20a%20means%20for%20people%20to%20die%20without%20the%20need%20for%20medical%20supervision.%20It%20releases%20nitrogen%20gas%20inside%20and%20reduces%20the%20oxygen%20levels%20to%20lethal%20amounts.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20Sarco%20pod%20is%20the%20brainchild%20of%20Philip%20Nitschke%2C%20an%20Australian%20physician%20known%20for%20his%20advocacy%20of%20assisted%20suicide%20since%20the%201990s.%20His%20work%20has%20played%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20the%20ongoing%20discussions%20around%20the%20ethics%20and%20legality%20of%20euthanasia%2C%20according%20to%20CNN.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%203D-printable%20Sarco%20capsule%20cost%20over%206%2C50%2C000%20euros%20(around%20Rs%206.06%20crore)%20to%20research%20and%20develop%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20over%2012%20years%2C%20according%20to%20AFP.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20the%20Sarco%20pod%20work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20Sarco%20pod%20replaces%20the%20oxygen%20inside%20with%20nitrogen%2C%20resulting%20in%20death%20by%20hypoxia.%20To%20operate%20the%20Sarco%20pod%2C%20the%20individual%20wishing%20to%20die%20must%20follow%20some%20steps%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETo%20use%20the%20Sarco%2C%20individuals%20must%20first%20pass%20a%20psychiatric%20assessment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUsers%20climb%20into%20the%20capsule%2C%20close%20the%20lid%2C%20and%20answer%20automated%20questions%20about%20their%20identity%20and%20understanding%20of%20the%20process.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOnce%20the%20button%20is%20pressed%2C%20the%20oxygen%20level%20in%20the%20capsule%20drops%20from%2021%25%20to%200.05%25%20in%20less%20than%2030%20seconds.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIndividuals%20quickly%20lose%20consciousness%20and%20die%20within%20approximately%20five%20minutes.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAn%20emergency%20exit%20button%20is%20also%20located%20inside%20the%20pod%2C%20providing%20a%20potential%20escape%20route%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOnce%20the%20hypoxia%20process%20is%20complete%2C%20the%20biodegradable%20capsule%20can%20be%20detached%20from%20the%20machine's%20base%2C%20allowing%20it%20to%20serve%20as%20the%20deceased%20individual's%20coffin.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitschke's%20Exit%20International%2C%20which%20owns%20the%20Sarco%2C%20is%20a%20non-profit%20organisation%20funded%20by%20donations%2C%20with%20users%20only%20paying%2018%20Swiss%20francs%20(around%20Rs%201%2C769)%20for%20the%20nitrogen.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EIts%20legality%20in%20Switzerland%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnSwitzerland%20has%20permitted%20assisted%20suicide%20since%20the%201940s%2C%20saying%20the%20ones%20assisting%20must%20have%20no%20direct%20interest%20in%20the%20i