was%2050%2C000%20years%20old%20instead%20of%20100%2C000.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BAt%20this%20time%2C%20the%20geneticists%20decided%20to%20calibrate%20their%20own%20tools%20and%20to%20change%20everything%20we%20knew%20about%20all%20Neanderthals%2C%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3Earchaeologist%20Ludovic%20Slimak%2C%20lead%20author%20on%20the%20new%20study%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fcell-genomics%2Ffulltext%2FS2666-979X(24)00177-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECell%20Genomics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%3Cspan%3ENamely%2C%20that%20they%20were%20all%20a%20part%20of%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsome-more-neanderthal-dna-others-scientists-why-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esingle%20homogenous%20population%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBecause%20of%20how%20different%20his%20DNA%20was%20from%20Neanderthals%20closer%20to%20his%20age%2C%20the%20researchers%20realized%20that%20Thorin%20must%20have%20belonged%20to%20a%20completely%20new%20Neanderthal%20lineage.%20They%20estimated%20his%20ancestors'%20line%20had%20split%20around%20103%2C000%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20explained%20why%20Thorin's%20DNA%20seemed%20so%20much%20more%20ancient%20than%20his%20bones.%20His%20DNA%20resembles%20Neanderthals%20who%20lived%20over%20100%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20Thorin%20was%2050%2C000%20years%20younger%2C%20according%20to%20the%20recent%20study.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20could%20have%20caused%20this%20genetic%20split%3F%20The%20researchers%20suspect%20that%20Thorin%20lived%20in%20an%20isolated%20community%20that%20had%20little%20to%20no%20contact%20with%20other%20groups%20from%20the%20time%20they%20diverged%20until%20Thorin's%20death.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20means%2C%20people%20within%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-interbreeding-between-humans-and-neanderthals-affects-our-health-today-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecommunity%20reproduced%20amongst%20themselves%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20more%20than%2050%2C000%20years%2C%20spawning%20a%20unique%20lineage%20distinct%20from%20other%20Neanderthal%20groups%2C%20according%20to%20the%20researchers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20you%20can%20imagine%2C%20a%20community%20isolated%20for%20that%20long%20will%20inevitably%20lead%20to%20inbreeding%2C%20and%20the%20researchers%20did%20indeed%20find%20evidence%20of%20that%20in%20Thorin's%20DNA.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20community's%20isolation%20also%20helps%20explain%20why%20Thorin%20was%20among%20the%20last%20of%20the%20Neanderthals.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscience-marry-your-cousin-safe-genetics-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EInbreeding%20leads%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20genetic%20diversity%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20can%20make%20populations%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20disease%2C%20harmful%20mutations%2C%20and%20environmental%20changes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20one%20isolated%20community%20can't%20speak%20for%20an%20entire%20species%2C%20it%20can%20point%20to%20a%20key%20behavior%20that%20sheds%20new%20light%20on%20why%20these%20human%20relatives%20died%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20this%20incredible%20extinction%2C%20which%20is%20the%20last%20great%20extinction%20of%20humanity%2C%26quot%3B%20Slimak%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ec65f9ab-25b6-4918-93fd-5d996ad2f4d7%5C%22%3ENeanderthals%20kept%20to%20themselves%2C%20which%20could%20help%20explain%20their%20extinction%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222003%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20Neanderthal%20skeletons%20on%20display%20at%20The%20Smithsonian%20Museum%20of%20Natural%20History%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cbd72294aa8ee8e84af524%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221585%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20pair%20of%20Neanderthal%20skeletons%20at%20The%20Smithsonian%20Museum%20of%20Natural%20History%20show%20how%20the%20species'%20body%20changed%20over%20thousands%20of%20years.%3Cp%3EBill%20O'Leary%2FThe%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThorin's%20community%20wasn't%20isolated%20because%20of%20geography.%20They%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fantisocial-personality-disorder%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eisolated%20because%20they%20chose%20to%20be%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Slimak%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20facing%20a%20border%2C%20a%20social%20border%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eother%20Neanderthals%20lived%20just%20a%20couple%20weeks'%20walk%20from%20Thorin's%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0277379121004480%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMassif%20Central%3C%2Fa%3E%20around%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Thorin's%20relatives%20did%20ignore%20their%20Neanderthal%20neighbors%2C%20that%20means%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmodern-loneliness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20group's%20isolation%3C%2Fa%3E%20wasn't%20only%20genetic%20but%20was%20also%20cultural%20and%20social%2C%20Slimak%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20very%20important%20and%20very%20central%20to%20understanding%20what%20was%20this%20population%20and%2C%20at%20the%20end%2C%20why%20and%20how%20they%20disappeared%20and%20they%20died%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Slimak%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20isolation%20may%20have%20worked%20for%20Thorins'%20ancestors%20for%20millennia%2C%20eventually%20their%20luck%20ran%20out.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20little%20social%20network%20just%20collapsed%20onto%20themselves%20and%20just%20died%20in%20a%20whisper%2C%26quot%3B%20Slimak%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226978ad0c-08c3-4f1e-9816-babb68840ad5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EModern%20humans'%20large%20social%20networks%20may%20have%20helped%20them%20survive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223968%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20model%20showing%20a%20Neanderthal%20family%20near%20a%20fire.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F56e71f809105842b008b6391%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222232%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20exhibit%20shows%20the%20life%20of%20a%20Neanderthal%20family%20in%20a%20cave%20at%20the%20Neanderthal%20Museum%20in%20Krapina%2C%20Croatia.%3Cp%3EReuters%2FNikola%20Solic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20universal%20this%20isolationist%20behavior%20among%20Neanderthals%20was%20is%20unclear.%20If%20resources%20in%20the%20area%20were%20scarce%2C%20the%20Neanderthals%20may%20have%20started%20becoming%20more%20insular%20to%20protect%20their%20own%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20this%20idea%20that%20one%20group%20kept%20to%20themselves%20maybe%20is%20not%20so%20crazy%20in%20that%20kind%20of%20competitive%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20April%20Nowell%2C%20a%20Paleolithic%20archaeologist%20with%20the%20University%20of%20Victoria%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20with%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Neanderthals'%20numbers%20dwindled%2C%20maintaining%20smaller%20and%20smaller%20groups%20would%20have%20put%20their%20future%20at%20risk%20whenever%20a%20family%20member%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20experts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D0dda9b208d7c44ccdb961bdb9c9a45661653c52f24e70106524b9f8725031266%26postID%3D66f340a28d7e7259bc9488b4%26postSlug%3Dlast-neanderthal-thorin-unique-dna-help-explain-species-extinction-2024-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-021-84410-7%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebelieve%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Neanderthals'%20small%20group%20sizes%20led%20to%20their%20extinction%2C%20which%20would%20have%20made%20them%20vulnerable%20even%20without%20added%20stressors%20like%20increased%20competition%20from%20humans.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20modern%20humans%20didn't%20seem%20to%20have%20had%20the%20same%20tendency%20to%20form%20insular%20communities.%20Instead%2C%20they%20traveled%20far%20and%20wide%20and%20formed%20large%20social%20networks%2C%20Slimak%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20modern%20human%20populations%20that%20seem%20to%20have%20these%20wider%20social%20networks%20and%20are%20exchanging%20genes%20with%20potential%20mates%20on%20a%20wider%20geographical%20region%2C%26quot%3B%20Nowell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EModern%20human%20groups%20were%20expanding%20and%20becoming%20more%20genetically%20diverse.%20That%20made%20them%20better%20equipped%20to%20handle%20any%20sort%20of%20accident%20or%20natural%20disaster%2C%20Nowell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20with%20smaller%20Neanderthal%20populations%2C%20even%20losing%20a%20handful%20of%20breeding-age%20individuals%20impacts%20future%20generations%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20really%20do%20think%20that%20the%20genetic%20isolation%20is%20telling%20us%20something%20interesting%20about%20Neanderthals%20and%20their%20challenges%20and%20eventually%20their%20extinction%2C%26quot%3B%20Nowell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flast-neanderthal-thorin-unique-dna-help-explain-species-extinction-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727304084000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f44814de59ade1a3b48e24%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessin